 COPS in Seshego outside Polokwane have bust two suspects aged 21
and 24 for kidnapping and killing a 22-year-old man. Police spokesperson Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said on 07 June 2019, cops
received a report about a group of community members who gathered at Moletjie
Ga-Makibelo village outside Seshego and they reacted immediately. He said on arrival, the Police found a man aged 22 lying on the
ground with serious injuries throughout his body. The victim was taken to the hospital for medical treatment where
he succumbed to his injuries. He was identified as Matsosa Kobo aged 22. This operation was immediately activated and started tracking the
suspects involved in this matter which led to the arrest of the two suspects. The suspects will appear before the Seshego Magistrate court soon
and more arrests are expected. The Provincial Commissioner of the South African Police Service in
Limpopo Lieutenant General Nneke Ledwaba has applauded the swift reaction by
members of the Police in arresting these suspects within a short space of time.  